See docs/user/clambc-user.pdf, chapter 1 "Installation".
Getting the bytecode compiler repository:
-----------------------------------------
git clone git://github.com/vrtadmin/clamav-bytecode-compiler

Quick start for building:
-------------------------
Check that your compiler version is not listed as a broken compiler here:
http://llvm.org/docs/GettingStarted.html#brokengcc

$ mkdir obj
$ cd obj
$ export CXXFLAGS=-std=c++11
$ ../llvm/configure --enable-optimized --enable-targets=host-only --disable-bindings --prefix=/usr/local/clamav
$ make clambc-only -j4
$ make install-clambc -j8

For building and running tests:
-------------------------------
$ mkdir obj
$ cd obj
$ export CXXFLAGS=-std=c++11
$ ../llvm/configure --enable-optimized --enable-targets=host-only --disable-bindings --prefix=/usr/local/clamav
$ make clambc-only -j4
$ make -j4
$ make check-all

See docs/user/clambc-user.pdf, section "1.3 Building" if build fails.

Staying up-to-date:
-------------------
git pull

Using a specific release:
-------------------------
$ git tag|grep ^clambc
clambc-0.10
$ git checkout clambc-0.10

Synchronizing clambcc with clamav
---------------------------------
Assuming you're starting from scratch:
1. clone clamav-devel and clamav-bytecode-compiler side by side.
2. Get a shell in an ubuntu:16.04 docker container:
   docker run -v (pwd)/clamav-bytecode-compiler:/clamav-bytecode-compiler -v (pwd)/clamav-upstream:/clamav-devel -it ubuntu:16.04 /bin/bash
3. Build the bytecode-compiler in the `obj` subdirectory (see above). Note: you'll probably need to install `gcc` and `make` first.
4. Build the examples with: `./compile_examples.sh`
5. Run the sync script from the compiler source directory: `./sync_clamav.sh`

Note: You can ignore the generated `./bytecode_api_impl.h` and `./bytecode_hooks.h` files.
These are generated with `ifacegen` and copied into the clamav repository.

Verifying signature on tag:
---------------------------
1. Get my GPG key (clamav.net/gpg/edwin.gpg)
2. Verify the tag:
$ git tag -v clambc-0.10

type commit
